UGHELLI – A frontline House of Representatives aspirant, Ughelli North, Ughelli South, Udu Federal Constituency under the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Chief Eunice Daji Okoh, has condoled with the families of those that lost their lives in a recent fire disaster at Ohorhor Community, Ughelli North Local Government Area of Delta State. Okoh who made this known when she visited the community, also sympathised with those that lost their houses and valuables in the fire disaster caused by an explosion from a tanker loaded with fuel. The popular aspirant urged authorities that are in charge of petroleum product tankers’ drivers to build parks for them in the area to avoid future occurrences of the incident. Rangnick Explains Lingard Stay Linked To Greenwood Adebomehin Appointed As Substantive SGoF According to her, the visit was to commiserate with victims of the fire disaster and called for the immediate evacuation of petroleum tankers from the area. She noted that a tankers park would also serve as a source of revenue to the state and local government area. She appealed to the three tiers of government, corporate organisations and public-spirited Nigerians to come to the aid of victims of the fire disaster.